## SESSION OUTPUT FORMAT

### FIX-SHIPPED outcome:

```
✅ Bug-hunt session [N] complete — FIX SHIPPED

**Tier**: P[0-5] — [name]
**Symptom**: [one sentence]
**Root cause**: [one sentence]
**Fix**: [one sentence]
**Files changed**: [list]
**Regression test**: [path::testname]
**Verification**: [vet pass | go test pass | npm test pass | lint pass | build pass]
**Git**: [branch] commit [short SHA] | push [ok / failed: reason]
**Next up**: [top queue item]
```

### CLEAN-STATE outcome:

```
✅ Bug-hunt session [N] complete — CODEBASE CLEAN

**Scanned**: P0, P1, P2, P3, P4, P5
**Verification**: [vet pass | go test pass | npm test pass]
**Audit log**: .agent/bug-hunting-agent.log (entry appended, no commit)
**SUSPECTED items recorded**: [count]
**Next up**: [carried-over queue head, or "(none — codebase clean)"]

No defects found within the scanned tiers. Stopping.
```

No essays. No explanations. Two outcomes, two formats. The user must be able to tell at a glance which happened.
